President Joe Biden has announced the recipients of the Presidential Awards for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching (PAEMST) and Presidential Awards for Excellence in Science, Mathematics and Engineering Mentoring (PAESMEM). These awards recognize the important role that teachers and mentors play in supporting learners who will become future STEM professionals. The awards honor their dedication and hard work in preparing students for careers in STEM fields. The recipients include teachers, mentors, and mentoring organizations from all 50 states, Washington D.C., Puerto Rico, U.S. territories, and Department of Defense Education Activity (DODEA) schools. The National Science Foundation manages the awards on behalf of the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP). Each recipient receives $10,000 and a certificate signed by the President.